[start section id="$final"]
Final Diagnosis
A. Serosa, small bowel implant, biopsy:  Granulation tissue with marked acute and chronic inflammation.  Negative for tumor.

B.  Serosa, small bowel implant #2, biopsy:  Granulation tissue with marked acute and chronic inflammation. Negative for malignancy.

C.  Peritoneum, pelvic rim, necrotic tumor, excision:  Moderately differentiated adenocarcinoma with patchy necrosis.

D.  Ileum, terminal and partial ascending colon, resection:  Multi-focal serosal involvement by moderately differentiated adenocarcinoma.  The mucosa of the ileum, appendix, and colon are unremarkable.  Multiple (5) regional lymph nodes are identified and are negative for malignancy. 



[end section id="$final"]
[start section id="$gross"]

Gross Description
A.  Received fresh labeled ""small bowel implant"" is a 1.1 x 1.0 x 0.9 cm fragment of pink tissue.  All submitted.  Grossed by DAY.

B.  Received fresh labeled ""small bowel implant #2"" is a 2.2 x 1.7 x 0.5 cm aggregate of pink-tan tissue.  All submitted.  Grossed by BOLDUC.

C.  Received fresh labeled ""? necrotic tumor"" is a 7.2 x 5.3 x 1.2 cm aggregate of pink hemorrhagic tissue.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by DAY.

D.  Received fresh labeled terminal ileum and partial ascending colon is a right hemicolectomy specimen consisting of 9.3 cm of terminal ileum, 8.3 cm of colon, and a 2.5 x 0.3 cm appendix. No mucosal lesions are identified. Also received are multiple irregular red tissue fragments measuring in aggregate, 5.5 x 4.3 x 1.2 cm. An anastomosis is present in the terminal ileum.  In the serosal surface of the ileum, multiple red firm adhesions are present, measuring up to 2.7 x 1.2 cm.  The appendix is grossly unremarkable.  Multiple lymph nodes are identified within the mesenteric fat. Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by DAY.




